  "text": "Male genitalia. Male genitalia of larentiines are relatively simple, characterized at the subfamily level by the loss of gnathos (except some genera of Trichopterygini) and the reduction of socii resulting in a shift of scaphium abductor musculature from socii to uncus [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] Kuznetsov and Stekolnikov 2001) .",
